          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "wang di",
          "email": "di.wang@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-07-29 08:06:09.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "subject": "LU-6928 ptlrpc: Do not pack min XID for connect req",
        "message": "LU-6928 ptlrpc: Do not pack min XID for connect req\n\nDo not pack min XID for connect request, because all of\nunreplied request may not in the sending/delay list at the\nmoment, for example replay request which is just timeout.\n\nAnd if it packs the wrong min(bigger than it should be) XID\nto the Server, and server will delete some reply data, which\nclient even do not know if the server receives, so the client\nmight resend the request, but server already delete the reply\ndata, so the request will be executed again.\n\nSigned-off-by: wang di <di.wang@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I43698ec64199319091f4840636be7b38a7ac6221\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
